00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
Science has a clearer story about solar wind pressure than social media does.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:12,000
Solar wind is a stream of charged particles from the sun, pushing through space at incredible speeds.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:14,800
But what does that mean for Earth?

4
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:19,200
Well, this pressure can affect our satellites and even create auroras!

5
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:24,000
Research shows fluctuations in solar wind can disrupt communications and power grids.

6
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:32,400
So, next time you hear about solar wind, remember: it’s not just a space phenomenon; it’s a force influencing our lives.

